We'II have to contact the store
and see if they want to press charges.

06:43.240 --> 06:47.119
- You know who I am?
- Yes, sir. Councillor Heslop.

06:47.240 --> 06:50.198
- Who are you?
- I'm Constable Saunders, and this is Constable Gillespie.

06:50.320 --> 06:54.313
Saunders? You're not
Graham Saunders' oldest boy, are you?

06:54.440 --> 06:56.670
- Brad.
- Young Brad.

06:56.800 --> 07:00.395
I haven't seen you since you played
fullback for the Porpoise Spit Giants!

07:00.520 --> 07:03.353
How's your dad? How's he
recovering from that stroke?

07:03.480 --> 07:05.516
- He's better than he was.
- You're terrible, Muriel.

07:05.640 --> 07:08.279
How about a beer? Cold one
before you go back to work?

07:08.400 --> 07:10.470
- Betty.
- Yes? What?

07:10.600 --> 07:13.353
- Get the young fellas a beer.
- Oh. Yes.

07:35.640 --> 07:38.029
You can dance

07:38.160 --> 07:40.355
You can jive

07:40.480 --> 07:43.950
Having the time of your life

07:44.080 --> 07:46.992
Ooh, see that girl

07:47.120 --> 07:49.315
Watch that scene

07:49.440 --> 07:53.319
Diggin' the dancing queen

07:59.600 --> 08:02.990
Friday night and the lights are low

08:04.480 --> 08:08.758
Looking out for a place to go

08:08.880 --> 08:11.474
- Where they play the right music
- See you, boys!

08:11.600 --> 08:13.477
- Getting in the swing
- See you, Bill.

08:13.600 --> 08:16.717
You come to look for a king

08:18.720 --> 08:22.998
Anybody could be that guy

08:23.120 --> 08:27.159
Night is young
and the music's high

08:29.760 --> 08:33.719
I think he'II enjoy that.
It's very good.

08:33.840 --> 08:37.309
Oh, honey prawns! Yes! Yum!

08:37.440 --> 08:41.513
Aw, look at that!
You're a wonderful man, Charlie Chan.

08:41.640 --> 08:43.312
- Thank you. - How's
your uncle? - Very well.

08:43.440 --> 08:46.273
I got his uncle out from China.
Talked to the boys from Immigration.

08:46.400 --> 08:49.437
Ian McKay and his blokes,
they got his uncle out from China.

08:49.560 --> 08:51.949
- This is a great man.
- Charlie.

08:52.080 --> 08:55.789
- This is Victor Keinosuke and his mate, uh, Akira.
- How do you do?

08:55.920 --> 08:57.956
They're building a resort
at Wallum Beach...

08:58.080 --> 09:01.629
and they might want a Chinese restaurant
in it, so keep the food comin'.

09:01.760 --> 09:04.320
- Please, please.
- Thank you. Thank you.

09:04.440 --> 09:07.193
It's all on the house.
I got his uncle out from China.

09:07.320 --> 09:09.709
You've done a lot for the people
of this town, Bill.

09:09.840 --> 09:12.035
- Who told you that?
- You did.

09:12.160 --> 09:16.119
Ah, well, um- I like helping out.
Ran for state government once.

09:16.240 --> 09:18.754
Joanie, stand up.
Show 'em your shirt.

09:21.840 --> 09:24.434
" Bill Heslop.
You can't stop progress. "

09:24.560 --> 09:29.111
- He lost.
- Yeah, well, missed on the postal vote.

09:29.240 --> 09:31.071
In a way, I'm glad
I didn't get in.

09:31.200 --> 09:33.395
I can do more for this place
at grass roots level.

09:33.520 --> 09:36.876
You know, high rise,
malls, resorts.

09:37.000 --> 09:42.074
Porpoise Spit Council
believes in progress. Muriel.

09:42.200 --> 09:45.875
When Victor was 19,
he was a millionaire.

09:46.000 --> 09:48.468
Muriel's on the dole.

09:48.600 --> 09:50.795
So is Perry.

09:50.920 --> 09:54.879
Well, I've got a job interview
next week. An apprentice locksmith.

09:55.000 --> 09:59.357
Oh, that sounds wonderful.
Doesn't it, Bill?

10:01.160 --> 10:03.628
A bit old for an apprentice,
aren't you?

10:03.760 --> 10:05.990
A bit old for everything!

10:06.120 --> 10:07.997
After she failed high school...

10:08.120 --> 10:10.714
I get her into a secretarial course
run by a mate of mine.

10:10.840 --> 10:15.630
$300 a term.
Two years, $2,000.

10:15.760 --> 10:18.718
- She comes out, she can't even type.
- I could type.

10:18.840 --> 10:21.149
Then I get her a job
at me solicitor's.

10:21.280 --> 10:24.556
After a month, Stevie Mason rings up
and says he'II have to let her go...

10:24.680 --> 10:26.557
'cause she can't type.

10:26.680 --> 10:29.513
If I couldn't type, why did they give me
my secretarial diploma?

10:29.640 --> 10:32.552
Because I paid for it!

10:32.680 --> 10:35.194
Sits around the house
like a dead weight...

10:35.320 --> 10:39.472
