17:07.000 --> 17:11.596
How can a man be so strong
and so fast? Heslop!

17:11.720 --> 17:13.597
Perry!

17:16.480 --> 17:18.357
Wake up to yourself!

17:22.079 --> 17:25.390
And Heslop's made a comeback!
How does he do it?

17:25.520 --> 17:28.159
- Did he apply for the police force?
- Yes, but they wouldn't let him sit for the test...

17:28.280 --> 17:31.317
'cause he was too tall.

17:31.440 --> 17:34.352
- Muriel up?
- Muriel!

17:34.480 --> 17:36.471
You've got to get up!
It's nearly 10:30!

17:36.600 --> 17:38.511
Make sure she sees Deidre Chambers
about that job.

17:38.640 --> 17:41.393
- Give her a blank cheque for the cosmetics.
- A blank cheque? How much for?

17:41.520 --> 17:44.353
It's a blank cheque. She fills in the
amount when Deidre tells her what it is.

17:44.480 --> 17:47.711
And tell Perry to mow that back yard.
Clean the place up. It's a pigsty.

17:47.840 --> 17:52.118
Joanie, will you turn off that television
and clean this place up? It's a pigsty.

17:52.240 --> 17:56.119
Muriel, you have to get up and go
and see Deidre Chambers about that job.

17:56.240 --> 17:59.835
- And I have to give you a blank cheque.
- Have you seen my smokes?

17:59.960 --> 18:02.474
It's wonderful for Deidre
to give you work.

18:02.600 --> 18:06.388
She's a wonderful person.
I don't care what anyone else says.

18:06.520 --> 18:10.559
- Mum?
- What who says?

18:10.680 --> 18:12.591
All those people
who've never liked Dad.

18:12.720 --> 18:15.314
Those greedies and those
terrible women at the post office.

18:15.440 --> 18:17.590
