44:23.600 --> 44:27.639
I mean, it's nothing to do
with too much sex, is it?

44:27.760 --> 44:31.355
No, no. Nothing like that.

44:31.480 --> 44:34.870
- We don't know what causes
cancer. - Cancer? - Cancer?

44:35.000 --> 44:37.878
You never said anything about cancer.

44:38.000 --> 44:42.118
- That's what the tumour is. It's a can-
- I've got cancer!

44:42.240 --> 44:45.357
Oh, God! I'm gonna go bald
and have to eat macrobiotic food!

44:45.480 --> 44:49.234
We're not talking about radiotherapy.
This is a discreet tumour.

44:49.360 --> 44:53.751
Alone. Isolated. The operation's
all we need for the moment.

44:53.880 --> 44:58.271
- For the moment?
- There's a minor risk of damage to the spinal cord.

44:58.400 --> 45:02.951
- What does that mean?
- It means I'm up shit creek, that's what it means.

45:58.960 --> 46:01.030
Silk chantel.

46:02.640 --> 46:05.632
Imported.

46:05.760 --> 46:08.433
When's your big day?

46:08.560 --> 46:11.757
Your wedding day?

46:11.880 --> 46:16.874
- September.
- Spring. Ivory.

46:54.240 --> 46:57.277
- What's your fiance's name?
- Bill.

46:57.400 --> 46:59.868
Well, Bill's
in for a big surprise.

47:00.000 --> 47:02.912
- Will your mother be coming to see the dress?
- No.

47:03.040 --> 47:06.555
No, she can't.
She's in hospital.

47:06.680 --> 47:09.558
She's got a tumour in her spine.

47:09.680 --> 47:12.148
She has to have an operation.

47:15.000 --> 47:17.560
We don't usually do this.

47:20.880 --> 47:23.269
But your mother has to see
how beautiful you look in that dress.

48:05.600 --> 48:08.160
Doing well.
Isn't she doing well, Mariel?

48:08.280 --> 48:10.840
- You're doing really well.
- Now this foot forward.

48:10.960 --> 48:14.555
You can do it. Good.

48:14.680 --> 48:17.148
Now the other one.

48:18.640 --> 48:21.154
Good. That's good.

48:22.960 --> 48:25.110
And-

48:29.360 --> 48:32.636
- I have to sit down.
- Come on.

48:32.760 --> 48:35.957
- I have to sit down!
- All right. I've got you.

48:37.680 --> 48:41.912
Don't panic. Swing around.

48:42.040 --> 48:45.350
That's it. Hand back.

48:45.480 --> 48:47.038
Take a break, honey.

48:47.160 --> 48:49.549
You're doing really well.

48:53.840 --> 48:56.559
How can you stand this?

48:56.680 --> 49:00.195
You push me around in this chair.
You cook for me.

49:00.320 --> 49:02.311
You even help me dress.
I hate it!

49:04.440 --> 49:07.034
When I lived in Porpoise Spit,
I'd just stay in my room for hours...

49:07.160 --> 49:09.515
and listen to ABBA songs.

49:09.640 --> 49:12.950
Sometimes I'd stay in there
all day.

49:13.080 --> 49:14.957
But since I've met you
and moved to Sydney...

49:15.080 --> 49:18.390
I haven't listened
to one ABBA song.

49:18.520 --> 49:21.990
It's because now my life's
as good as an ABBA song.

49:22.120 --> 49:24.554
It's as good as " Dancing Queen. "

49:26.160 --> 49:28.151
Come off it.

49:32.360 --> 49:34.078
Promise me something.

49:34.200 --> 49:38.398
- We never go back there.
- What do you mean?

49:38.520 --> 49:42.433
I mean, I can't go back
and live in Porpoise Spit with Mum.

49:42.560 --> 49:45.950
- Not in a wheelchair, not with her.
- You're gonna walk.

49:47.480 --> 49:50.278
Promise we never go back.

49:50.400 --> 49:52.755
I promise.

49:55.360 --> 49:58.352
But you're gonna walk.

50:10.280 --> 50:12.555
I believe
there's something out there.

50:12.680 --> 50:15.877
- Yeah. I'm-I'm not a sceptic about it.
- I've been cheated by you

50:16.000 --> 50:21.074
- Since I don't know when
- Too many people have seen it. There's been too much documentation.

50:21.200 --> 50:22.758
So I made up my mind

50:22.880 --> 50:26.350
- It must come to an end
- Taxi for the rehabilitation centre?

50:26.480 --> 50:29.438
- Hang on. I have to get my
smokes. - Look at me now - Okay.

50:29.560 --> 50:33.030
Will I ever learn
I don't know how

50:33.160 --> 50:36.232
But I suddenly lose control

50:36.360 --> 50:39.875
There's a fire within my soul

50:40.000 --> 50:43.231
Just one look
and I can hear a bell ring

50:43.360 --> 50:46.750
One more look
and I forget everything

50:46.880 --> 50:51.351
Oh-oh-oh, Mamma mia
Here I go again

50:51.480 --> 50:54.631
My, my, how can I resist you

50:54.760 --> 50:58.036
Mamma mia, does it show again

50:58.160 --> 51:01.391
My, my, just how much
I've missed you

51:01.520 --> 51:04.796
Yes, I've been broken-hearted

51:04.920 --> 51:08.071
Blue since the day we parted

51:08.200 --> 51:11.431
Why, why did I ever let you go

51:11.560 --> 51:14.836
Mamma Mia, now I really know

51:14.960 --> 51:18.157
My, my, I could never let you go

51:24.840 --> 51:28.753
I've been angry and sad
about things that you do

51:31.520 --> 51:35.433
I can't count all the times
that I've told you we're through

51:38.280 --> 51:41.431
- And when you go When you slam the door
- Keep going.

51:41.560 --> 51:46.759
I think you know
that you won't be away too long

51:46.880 --> 51:50.634
You know that I'm not that strong

51:50.760 --> 51:53.672
- Just one look and I can hear-
- Stop the car!

51:57.600 --> 51:59.670
Beautiful.

52:01.280 --> 52:05.273
I hope the photos help your sister
out of that coma.

52:05.400 --> 52:09.313
- Mariel! What are you doing?
- No-Nothing.

52:09.440 --> 52:11.431
Why didn't you tell me
you were gonna marry Tim?

52:11.560 --> 52:15.758
- Who? - Tim Simms, your fiance-
the one who wants to shoot you.

52:15.880 --> 52:19.077
Now, now, now, now just a minute. You
can't come in here and threaten brides.

52:19.200 --> 52:21.839
- I don't care how unfortunate you are.
- Fuck off.

52:21.960 --> 52:24.918
What is going on, Mariel?

52:25.040 --> 52:27.918
I've seen your wedding album.
You've tried on every dress in Sydney.

52:28.040 --> 52:30.713
- That doesn't mean I'm getting married.
- What else does it mean?

52:30.840 --> 52:34.150
I wanna get married.
I've always wanted to get married.

52:34.280 --> 52:37.397
If I can get married, it means
I've changed- I'm a new person.

52:37.520 --> 52:41.229
- How?
- Because who would want to marry me?

52:43.720 --> 52:47.599
- Tim Simms.
- There is no Tim Simms. I made him up.

52:47.720 --> 52:50.280
In Porpoise Spit,
no one would even look at me.

52:50.400 --> 52:53.597
But when I came to Sydney
and became Mariel, Brice asked me out.

52:53.720 --> 52:55.995
And that proves
I'm already different than I was...

52:56.120 --> 52:58.554
and if someone wants to marry me,
I'm not her any more.

52:58.680 --> 53:00.716
- I'm me.
- Her?

53:00.840 --> 53:03.070
Muriel! Muriel Heslop!

53:03.200 --> 53:05.919
Stupid, fat and useless!
I hate her!

53:06.040 --> 53:09.157
I'm not going back
to being her again!

53:11.560 --> 53:13.835
Why can't it be me?

53:15.160 --> 53:17.355
Why can't I be the one?

53:25.920 --> 53:28.354
Have you been in a coma?

53:53.760 --> 53:55.830
Rhonda?

53:57.280 --> 53:59.430
Dad.

54:02.560 --> 54:05.154
If they have a copy of this document,
then the option is...

54:05.280 --> 54:08.556
giving you a doctor's certificate
saying you are unfit to testify.

54:08.680 --> 54:11.752
Can I have that title deed, Paul?
That's the one.

54:11.880 --> 54:15.714
We can only assume that Victor Keinosuke
has given them a copy of this deed.

54:15.840 --> 54:18.991
Muriel, why'd you do it to me?

54:19.120 --> 54:21.634
I gave you money. I got you jobs.

54:21.760 --> 54:24.035
I put her through
this secretarial course.

54:24.160 --> 54:26.628
$2,000 for two years, it cost me.

54:26.760 --> 54:28.830
Comes out, she can't even type.

54:28.960 --> 54:31.679
I get her into selling cosmetics.
We all think she's making a go of it.

54:31.800 --> 54:36.112
Turns out she's robbin' us blind.
You're a disgrace, an absolute disgrace!

54:36.240 --> 54:39.232
A- Are you Bill the Battler?

54:39.360 --> 54:42.909
I saw you on TV.
Can I please have your autograph?

54:43.040 --> 54:45.315
Me and my dad think
that you're not guilty, Bill.

54:45.440 --> 54:47.510
I've changed my name to Mariel.

54:47.640 --> 54:50.108
Good on you, son.
You spread it around.

54:50.240 --> 54:53.596
You can't stop progress!

54:53.720 --> 54:56.029
You're comin' back to Porpoise Spit
with me.

54:56.160 --> 54:58.720
We'II leave in three weeks,
once this inquiry crap's over.

54:58.840 --> 55:01.308
- I can't go back. I'm a new person.
- You're a thief.

55:01.440 --> 55:05.149
The only reason I never got the coppers
onto you is your mother begged me not to.

55:05.280 --> 55:08.113
I want that money back.
I'II get you a job at the Leagues Club.

55:08.240 --> 55:09.639
I'II arrange a bank loan for you.

55:09.760 --> 55:11.955
You're going to make up
for what you've done, Muriel.

55:14.560 --> 55:19.509
It's Deidre Chambers.
Deidre! Deidre!

55:19.640 --> 55:22.712
Hey, Deidre!

55:22.840 --> 55:26.515
Bill!

55:26.640 --> 55:28.631
What a coincidence!
What are you doing in Sydney?

55:28.760 --> 55:30.955
Well, my sister lives in Sydney.
I'm down for the long weekend.

55:31.080 --> 55:33.548
- Pull up a chair. - What a coincidence!
- My barrister, Graham Newman.

55:33.680 --> 55:35.477
- His two solicitors, and Muriel you know about.
- Hello.

55:35.600 --> 55:38.637
It's Mariel!

55:40.000 --> 55:44.551
We should get back, Bill. Victor
Keinosuke's testimony starts at 3:00.

55:44.680 --> 55:47.240
That Jap bastard! He's gonna testify
that I took bribes from him.

55:47.360 --> 55:51.148
- Commissions.
- Commissions. I took commissions.

55:51.280 --> 55:54.795
Cut through all that red tape for him.
I deserve some sort of acknowledgement.

55:54.920 --> 55:57.309
They'd never have got to build
that resort on Crown Land without me.

55:57.440 --> 56:00.159
- It was the Crown Land that did it.
- Total overreaction.

56:00.280 --> 56:04.114
- There were aboriginals living on it.
- The federal police raided the house.

56:04.240 --> 56:05.958
Your mother just let them walk in.

56:06.080 --> 56:08.230
She and Perry made statements-
told them I had money problems.

56:08.360 --> 56:10.635
- Don't think about it.
- Of course I had money problems.

56:10.760 --> 56:13.228
- She stole most of it.
- You need your family around you.

56:13.360 --> 56:15.351
If the Feds come near you,
don't you say a word.

56:15.480 --> 56:19.109
- Are you and Deidre together?
- What?

56:22.280 --> 56:24.475
Have you left Mum for Deidre?

56:29.600 --> 56:33.229
Yes. We're in love.

56:38.280 --> 56:39.998
What about Mum?

56:42.760 --> 56:46.070
What happiness has your father had
in his life if he doesn't have me?

56:46.200 --> 56:49.078
- What about Mum?
- She'II have you.

56:49.200 --> 56:51.350
You got three weeks.

57:11.160 --> 57:15.119
It's come back- the tumour.

57:17.200 --> 57:20.749
I have to have another operation.

57:20.880 --> 57:22.757
I'm not gonna walk.

57:24.600 --> 57:28.388
But what about
your rehabilitation?

57:30.480 --> 57:33.278
They're gonna cut
my spinal cord, Mariel.

57:35.920 --> 57:37.911
Mum called.

57:38.040 --> 57:42.238
She wants to take me back
to Porpoise Spit.

57:42.360 --> 57:45.272
I told her I was gonna
stay here with you.

58:17.760 --> 58:21.673
Head down! Head down!
Come on! Come on! Swing it!

58:21.800 --> 58:25.588
Blokes with no legs and no arms
cut through the water faster than that!

58:25.720 --> 58:28.553
Look at that! You're going through there
like a constipated duck!

58:28.680 --> 58:31.513
Look at 'em flopping around
all over the place!

58:31.640 --> 58:34.074
Burchett, what do you think this is,
synchronized swimming?

58:34.200 --> 58:37.590
Water aerobics for geriatrics?
You're supposed to be a sprinter!

58:37.720 --> 58:39.233
Go! Go! Go! Go!

58:42.000 --> 58:43.911
Mariel?

58:45.400 --> 58:48.358
Ken Blundell. How are ya?

58:49.320 --> 58:50.992
Van Arkle!

58:55.000 --> 58:58.151
I think we found you a girl.

59:09.080 --> 59:11.913
David Van Arkle, Mariel Heslop.

59:20.760 --> 59:24.469
Mariel, you've probably seen the news
about the civil war in South Africa.

59:24.600 --> 59:27.717
Well, just as the South Africans seem to
be doing the right thing by the blacks...

59:27.840 --> 59:31.674
the police open fire on a black soccer
club, and that is bad news for David.

59:32.760 --> 59:36.833
- Are you black?
- What?

59:39.680 --> 59:41.830
I don't know why I said that.

59:41.960 --> 59:44.349
Well, well, it is funny, in a way.

59:44.480 --> 59:47.756
But let's be honest. The South Africans
were never much chop in the pool anyway.

59:47.880 --> 59:50.075
David here
is a bit of a freak, really.

59:50.200 --> 59:52.395
And I think that he is gonna get
the gold medal...

59:52.520 --> 59:56.877
for the 1,500 metres
in the next Olympic Games.

59:57.000 --> 59:59.560
Mariel, how did you feel
when Kieren Perkins...

59:59.680 --> 01:00:01.557
took gold for Australia
at Barcelona?

01:00:03.600 --> 01:00:07.752
- Who?
- Kieren Perkins.

01:00:07.880 --> 01:00:09.916
- He's an Australian champion.
- Now, David's family...

01:00:10.040 --> 01:00:13.669
are willing to do anything to see him
fulfil his potential as a champion...

01:00:13.800 --> 01:00:16.439
even if it means swimming
for another country.

01:00:16.560 --> 01:00:20.109
And they're willing to pay
$10,000...

01:00:20.240 --> 01:00:23.471
to the girl that'II help Dave out.

01:00:23.600 --> 01:00:27.275
Are you from Sydney originally?

01:00:27.400 --> 01:00:30.119
What? No, Porpoise Spit.

01:00:30.240 --> 01:00:32.913
A- And why did you leave there?

01:00:33.040 --> 01:00:37.830
Well, because of all the mental things
that happened to me.

01:00:37.960 --> 01:00:42.192
I got shallow, and my physical being
could have been improved...

01:00:42.320 --> 01:00:44.788
and as well as my mentality.

01:00:44.920 --> 01:00:46.831
- What about the black-haired one?
- No, she was Turkish.

01:00:46.960 --> 01:00:48.916
She's only been in the country
five minutes.

01:00:49.040 --> 01:00:51.315
Now, whoever marries David
will have to...

01:00:51.440 --> 01:00:53.715
tell the immigration authorities
that they're in love with him.

01:00:53.840 --> 01:00:55.831
Now there'II be media attention...

01:00:55.960 --> 01:00:58.474
so they'II have to live with David
in his flat...

01:00:58.600 --> 01:01:01.558
for at least four months
after the marriage.

01:01:01.680 --> 01:01:04.035
I've worked out all the details
of the romance...

01:01:04.160 --> 01:01:06.469
which you and David
will have to stick to.

01:01:06.600 --> 01:01:08.955
But the most important thing
is to convince people...

01:01:09.080 --> 01:01:11.275
that you two are really in love.

01:01:11.400 --> 01:01:12.992
- What about the blonde?
- You didn't like her.

01:01:13.120 --> 01:01:16.237
- I'm not so sure now.
- Now, I think Mariel might be...

01:01:16.360 --> 01:01:19.193
just what we're looking for.

01:01:19.320 --> 01:01:23.074
Well, it's up to you now, love.
Would you find it difficult to lie?

01:01:24.680 --> 01:01:26.716
I could try.

01:01:26.840 --> 01:01:28.637
Well, don't rush your decision...

01:01:28.760 --> 01:01:31.513
but if you could let us know
by tomorrow morning.

01:02:38.640 --> 01:02:42.952
You can dance, you can jive

01:02:43.080 --> 01:02:46.277
Having the time of your life

01:02:46.400 --> 01:02:51.269
Ooh, see that girl
Watch that scene

01:02:51.400 --> 01:02:55.757
Diggin' the dancing queen

01:03:27.480 --> 01:03:30.597
I know you couldn't have got up onto the altar, but
at least she could have asked you to be bridesmaid.

01:03:30.720 --> 01:03:34.110
- She did.
- Why didn't you say yes?

01:03:34.240 --> 01:03:36.037
You could have been on television.

01:03:36.160 --> 01:03:38.151
I don't want to sit up here, Mum.

01:03:38.280 --> 01:03:41.955
- I wanna sit in the corner.
- No one'II see you over there.

01:03:44.280 --> 01:03:46.874
Well, if this is your attitude,
I don't know why you bothered coming.

01:03:53.880 --> 01:03:56.872
At least you won't
be in anyone's way.

01:04:09.760 --> 01:04:11.830
Rhonda?

01:04:14.320 --> 01:04:16.117
Is that you?

01:04:18.360 --> 01:04:21.557
- You're the bridesmaids?
- Isn't it fantastic?

01:04:21.680 --> 01:04:24.990
- We always knew Mariel'd come good.
- She's in all the papers.

01:04:25.120 --> 01:04:28.715
- What happened to you?
- I had cancer.

01:04:28.840 --> 01:04:33.356
It's all right. They cut it out.
I won't walk again though.

01:04:34.960 --> 01:04:39.476
- You were so full of life.
- I'm not dead, Cheryl.

01:04:41.120 --> 01:04:44.635
Come on. We better get ready.
Mariel's coming.

01:04:44.760 --> 01:04:47.638
You must be so happy for her.

01:04:50.120 --> 01:04:52.395
God, she has cancer!

01:04:52.520 --> 01:04:55.034
I'm divorcing Chook.

01:04:55.160 --> 01:04:57.913
I suppose I have you
to thank for that.

01:04:58.040 --> 01:05:01.350
I hope I can do the same
for you one day.

01:05:22.960 --> 01:05:25.713
You told me it would be
a quick civil ceremony.

01:05:25.840 --> 01:05:28.229
Ah, it's good she wanted
a church wedding. It's romantic.

01:05:28.360 --> 01:05:31.113
It looks like you mean it.

01:05:31.240 --> 01:05:34.915
All the guests are on her side.
I should have hired you some friends.

01:05:35.040 --> 01:05:36.837
The charges don't surprise me.

01:05:36.960 --> 01:05:38.757
The bastards have been out to get me
from the beginnin'.

01:05:38.880 --> 01:05:40.677
I just wanted you to know-

01:05:46.760 --> 01:05:49.035
Mariel, are you marrying David
for money?

01:05:49.160 --> 01:05:51.355
Is this a marriage
of convenience, Mariel?

01:05:51.480 --> 01:05:53.357
Mariel, how long have you and David-

01:05:53.480 --> 01:05:56.756
Your Mum's arriving in Sydney by bus
because I can't afford a plane ticket.

01:05:56.880 --> 01:05:58.677
- You see what you've done to me?
- Where is she now?

01:05:58.800 --> 01:06:00.631
I don't know.
Trying to get a taxi, I suppose.

01:06:12.120 --> 01:06:14.509
Mariel.

01:06:14.640 --> 01:06:16.437
You're beautiful.

01:06:58.160 --> 01:07:01.038
Love me or leave me

01:07:01.160 --> 01:07:05.597
Make your choice, but believe me

01:07:05.720 --> 01:07:08.154
I love you

01:07:08.280 --> 01:07:12.398
I do, I do, I do, I do, I do

01:07:14.800 --> 01:07:17.792
I can't conceal it

01:07:17.920 --> 01:07:22.038
Don't you see
Can't you feel it

01:07:22.160 --> 01:07:24.674
Don't you too

01:07:24.800 --> 01:07:28.873
I do, I do, I do, I do, I do

01:07:30.800 --> 01:07:34.190
Oh, I've been dreaming

01:07:34.320 --> 01:07:40.270
Through my lonely past

01:07:40.400 --> 01:07:43.392
Now I just made it

01:07:43.520 --> 01:07:46.910
I've found you at last

01:07:47.040 --> 01:07:50.794
So come on now
Let's try it

01:07:50.920 --> 01:07:55.038
I love you, you can't deny it

01:07:55.160 --> 01:07:56.878
- 'Cause it's true
- Oh, God.

01:07:57.000 --> 01:08:02.279
- Don't panic. Think of the games.
- I do, I do, I do, I do, I do

01:08:04.600 --> 01:08:06.397
She's all yours, mate.

01:08:13.800 --> 01:08:18.350
Father, when You created mankind, You
willed that man and wife should be one.

01:08:18.479 --> 01:08:21.278
- Join David and Muriel-
- Mariel.

01:08:21.399 --> 01:08:24.278
Mariel in the loving union
of marriage...

01:08:24.399 --> 01:08:26.993
so that they may be living witness
to Your divine love in the world.

01:08:28.720 --> 01:08:31.154
David, do you take Mariel
to be your wife?

01:08:31.279 --> 01:08:33.794
Do you promise to be true to her
in good times and in bad...

01:08:33.920 --> 01:08:37.959
in sickness and in health- to love and
honour her all the days of your life?

